{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"final_filename: p20.cir\n\nObjective: create a 5 V single-supply two-stage differential opamp netlist with all MOSFETs conducting at the DC operating point. The first stage must be an NMOS differential pair with PMOS current-mirror active load and an NMOS tail current source. The second stage must be a common-source gain stage with an active load. The named inputs Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, and Vbias3 must all be explicitly driven by independent voltage sources, and the output nodes Voutp and Vout must both appear in the netlist.\n\nTopology: use VDD = 5 V and ground node 0. First stage is M1/M2 NMOS differential pair with common source node connected to tail NMOS M5. M3/M4 are PMOS active-load devices forming a current-mirror load at the drains of M1/M2. The first-stage high-impedance single-ended output should be node Voutp at the drain of M2 and M4. The diode-connected mirror side should be the drain/gate connection of M3 at the drain of M1, and M4 gate should connect to the same mirror gate node. This makes Voutp rise/fall with the differential input and provides first-stage voltage gain.\n\nRequired devices: M1 and M2 are NMOS input devices using model NMOS, W=50u, L=1u, with bulks tied to their common source node. M3 and M4 are PMOS active loads using model PMOS, W=100u, L=1u, with sources and bulks tied to VDD. M5 is the NMOS tail source using model NMOS, W=50u, L=1u, drain at the differential pair source node, source/bulk at 0, gate driven by Vbias1. Second stage should use NMOS M6 as common-source amplifier, gate driven by Voutp, source/bulk at 0, drain at Vout. Use PMOS M7 as active load for M6, source/bulk at VDD, drain at Vout, gate driven by Vbias2. Include an additional bias-connected MOS device or benign bias load using Vbias3 so that Vbias3 is present and electrically meaningful without disturbing the main opamp; preferably use Vbias3 as the gate of a small NMOS sink or PMOS bias helper tied so it conducts at DC and does not short critical gain nodes.\n\nBiasing assumptions: explicitly drive Vinp and Vinn to 2.5 V DC for balanced operation. Drive Vbias1 to about 1.1 V to create a threshold-aware NMOS tail current with M5 on but not excessive. Drive Vbias2 to about 3.8 V for a PMOS active load in the second stage, giving M7 VSG around 1.2 V so it conducts from VDD into Vout. Drive Vbias3 to a valid DC level such as 1.1 V for any auxiliary NMOS bias device or 3.8 V for any auxiliary PMOS bias device. Avoid floating nodes. Tie MOS bulks to sources as required.\n\nOperating-point intent: at Vinp = Vinn = 2.5 V, M1 and M2 split the M5 tail current. M3 diode-connects to set the PMOS mirror current and M4 mirrors that current into Voutp. Voutp should settle to a real high-impedance first-stage gain node, not hard rail. M6 and M7 must both conduct so Vout is also a real gain node with DC voltage between ground and VDD. The chosen bias voltages should keep every MOSFET above threshold and avoid dead branches.\n\nRequired analyses: include `.op`. The downstream netlist should define the NMOS and PMOS models with the specified threshold and transconductance parameters: NMOS Vth = 0.7 V, kp = 100u, W = 50u, L = 1u; PMOS Vth = -0.7 V, kp = 50u, W = 100u, L = 1u. Use nominal sizing unless extra balancing is needed for valid operating point.\n\nOutput constraints: final netlist file must be named `p20.cir`. The exact nodes Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, Vbias3, Voutp, and Vout must appear in the final netlist. Vinp, Vinn, Vbias1, Vbias2, and Vbias3 must each be driven by explicit independent voltage sources. Voutp is the first-stage output/interstage node, and Vout is the final opamp output."}}
